TITLE: Pelicans' Zion Williamson commits to slam dunk contest, pending NBA All-Star selection
SUMMARY: New Orleans Pelicans star forward Zion Williamson's commitment to the NBA Slam Dunk Contest is contingent on his inclusion in the All-Star game.

TITLE: San Francisco 'can no longer be called progressive city,' newspaper declares after law-and-order measures pass
SUMMARY: A article in the San Francisco Chronicle stated the city can't be called "progressive" anymore after its residents voted for two "moderate" ballots measures on Tuesday.

TITLE: Brittany Mahomes gives warning to all mothers after revealing she has fractured back
SUMMARY: Brittany Mahomes, the wife of Kansas City Chiefs quarterback Patrick Mahomes, revealed via Instagram she has a fractured back and gave a warning to all mothers.

TITLE: Whale that vanished from Atlantic over 200 years ago spotted off Massachusetts: 'Shouldn't exist'
SUMMARY: A team of scientists from the New England Aquarium in Boston spotted a rare gray whale swimming about 30 miles off the coast of Nantucket on Friday.

TITLE: Mark Wahlberg's brother, Donnie, spent $500,000 to help him launch career: 'Was going nowhere fast'
SUMMARY: Donnie Wahlberg invested hundreds of thousands of dollars into younger brother Mark in the early days of the Marky Mark rapper's career, telling him, "Don't waste my money."

TITLE: Former Utah school bus driver accused of setting fire to buses, including one with children on board: DOJ
SUMMARY: According to the Department of Justice, a 58-year-old former Utah bus driver faces arson charges after he allegedly lit his school bus on fire with at least 42 children inside.

TITLE: Ex-Chiefs star Tyreek Hill recalls time Patrick Mahomes called out teammates: 'He was letting me have it'
SUMMARY: Tyreek Hill and Patrick Mahomes were once considered the top duo in the NFL. Hill not only marveled at Mahomes physical traits, he also appreciated the QB's leadership.

TITLE: Two WWII-era bazooka rounds found in Massachusetts town river in the same week via magnet fishing
Former Cowboys tight end says team's facility is 'a zoo,' current team's 'focus is just football'
SUMMARY: Jerry Jones has built an empire with the Dallas Cowboys, but that empire has spread far beyond the football field, which Dalton Schultz doesn't seem to be a fan of.

TITLE: Panthers won't entertain Russell Wilson free agency sweepstakes, new head coach says
SUMMARY: Carolina Panthers new head coach Dave Canales is already making his team's intentions clear when it comes to the Russell Wilson sweepstakes in free agency.

TITLE: Philadelphia bus stop shooting critically injures high school student, 7 others wounded
SUMMARY: A Philadelphia bus station shooting on Wednesday resulted in eight high school students being struck by gunfire, with one listed in critical condition in a nearby hospital.

TITLE: Sen. Tom Cotton dunks on NY Times as paper reports Hochul is sending troops to NYC to combat crime
SUMMARY: The New York Times faced ire on social media while reporting that New York Gov. Kathy Hochul plans to send the National Guard to NYC subways to combat crime.

TITLE: LAURA INGRAHAM: Trump has nailed it on every major issue now
SUMMARY: Fox News host Laura Ingraham says reelecting President Biden means "more borders, more debt, lower wages and more racial division" on "The Ingraham Angle."

TITLE: All hands effort underway to help ranchers devastated by Texas Panhandle wildfires
SUMMARY: Ranchers and non-profit groups are pooling their resources together to truck in resources to ranchers in the Texas Panhandle who have been devastated by wildfires in the area.

TITLE: White shark's 2,000-mile journey from South Carolina to Gulf of Mexico makes history: 'She kept charging'
SUMMARY: Researchers said that LeeBeth the shark is the furthest west a white shark has been tracked in the Gulf of Mexico, and that the shark's journey was over 2,000 miles.

TITLE: Fentanyl overdose, stroke blamed for 2 of 4 recent deaths at troubled Wisconsin prison
SUMMARY: Two of the four inmates who died at Wisconsin's Waupun Correctional Institution since June died of a fentanyl overdose and a stroke, according to a medical examiner.

TITLE: Louisiana Gov. Landry issues disaster declaration amid crawfish shortage
SUMMARY: Republican Louisiana Gov. Jeff Landry on Wednesday issued a disaster declaration for the crawfish industry, citing an ongoing shortage.

TITLE: Alec Baldwin's 'Rust' armorer convicted of involuntary manslaughter
SUMMARY: 'Rust' armorer Hannah Gutierrez Reed was found guilty of involuntary manslaughter in the fatal shooting of cinematographer Halyna Hutchins.

TITLE: Biden sanctuary city pivot puts vulnerable Senate Democrats' stances in spotlight
SUMMARY: Vulnerable Democratic senators who are up for re-election in November are having to balance their past voting record with their claims they do not support sanctuary cities.

TITLE: Hamas hostages, IVF activists, cops attacked by migrants: These are lawmakers' State of the Union guests
SUMMARY: Members of Congress announced their guests to President Biden's upcoming State of the Union address, many of whom relate to current pressing issues, such as border security, IVF and Israel aid.

TITLE: Man who crashed into Washington State Patrol trooper, killing him, in US illegally: ICE
SUMMARY: U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) Seattle placed a detainer on a Mexican citizen in the country illegally after he was arrested and charged with killing a Washington State Patrol trooper in car crash Saturday.

TITLE: Trump maintains grip on GOP nod with victory in North Dakota caucuses
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump notched yet another primary victory on Monday, this time winning the North Dakota Caucuses that took place on the eve of "Super Tuesday."

TITLE: Legal experts rally around Supreme Court ruling keeping Trump on ballot: 'Stern warning' to 'radicals'
SUMMARY: Legal scholars weighed in Monday after the Supreme Court unanimously sided with former President Trump against an effort in Colorado to remove him from the ballot.

TITLE: Michael Moore claims Michigan uncommitted vote trying to 'save Biden from himself': 'Working against' Dems
SUMMARY: Michael Moore, a liberal activist, told MSNBC on Saturday that the uncommitted vote in Michigan, which he helped organize, was to save Biden from himself.

TITLE: Trump leads Biden among voters who favored Biden by 10 points in 2020: poll
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump holds a five-point lead over President Biden in a new New York Times poll among voters who favored Biden by 10 percentage points in 2020.
